				\begin{document}$$ Y \prime \left( {i,j} \right) = \frac{RefSD}{SD} \times \left\{ {Y\left( {i,j} \right) - {\rm Mean} } \right\} + {\rm RefMean} $$\end{document}where Y(i,j) is the brightness value of a picture before correction is provided and (i,j) is a coordinate of a given pixel.
